FBIS4-64923 "drweu090_k_94002" FBIS-WEU-94-090 Daily Report 6 May 1994 PORTUGAL Mozambique Asks For Help in Training Military Police Mozambique Asks For Help in Training Military Police LD0605200794 Lisbon Radio Renascenca in Portuguese to Europe 1900 GMT 6 May 94 LD0605200794 Lisbon Radio Renascenca Portuguese BFN [Text] Mozambique has asked Portugal to help with training its military police. The Maputo government and Renamo today asked Portugal to organize the new military police and to run another two leadership training programs for the new Mozambican Army. The Portuguese military mission in Mozambique has already come up with a specific program for training the police force and has already drawn up the curriculum for the new leadership courses.
